				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">NTSC VBlank is 20 scanlines:
<br />
<br />20 * 341 = 6820 PPU cycles
<br />
<br />/ 3 = 2273.333333  CPU cycles
<br />
<br />
<br />My understanding is you raise the VBlank flag at the very start of VBlank (and trigger an NMI if enabled) -- then you clear all $2002 flags immediately after those 20 scanlines are complete.  This is what my emu does and it passes all these tests.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

